The profile belongs to a friend of ours who is one of the sweetest and admirable persons we have in our circle. Very unfortunately he was divorced after a very brief marriage of few weeks in 2005. It didn?t last more than a few weeks because of extreme incompatibility and a hassle free divorce by mutual consent followed soon after. Though extremely disappointed he has finally agreed to look at life afresh after persistent pressure from family and friends and we would like our friend to be settled as early as possible and enjoy a blissful married life which he rightly and richly deserves.

He is an M.B.A and works in a senior position in a MNC Firm and has a successful career during which he been posted in various places in India and had a short stint abroad. Despite a fair amount of national and international travelling he is pretty attached to his roots and would probably try out entrepreneurial ventures of his own some day.
 
He has a multifarious and rounded personality and stands out in any crowd. He is an avid reader and is at home with most subjects and in any setting. He has a strong cultural grounding and very refined tastes enjoys a wide range of music and arts starting from modern pop and blues to classical music and cultural events. He enjoys traveling and is passionate about outdoors, nature and wildlife. He used to be good sportsperson in school and college and has extremely high energy levels and is a born athlete. On the looks front he is tall, fair and pretty good looking and looks much younger than his age. He used to carry the tag of the most eligible bachelor of the group until the ill fated accident in his circle. Beyond everything he has a very high sense of moral values and a steadfast determination of sticking to principles. Although he has a modern outlook he also has a strong Indian value system and still believes in the concept of a happy married life and lifelong companionship based on the simple tenets of sharing common goals and bringing up a happy family. He is crazy about children and is the favorite uncle of all his nephews and nieces and little children around.

He is the only son of his family and his father after retirement as a senior officer in the government service tragically passed away a year after retirement. That is also a reason why he had earlier put on hold his marriage to stabilise the family. His mother is a very simple, sweet and affectionate home maker who alternates her time between his sisters and Bhubaneshwar. He has two very lovable younger sisters who are happily married and very well settled. They belong to a very cultured and highly respected family of Orissa now settled in Bhubaneshwar where he has his own house

Since this would be an arranged marriage, it's imminent that the respective families be involved in this discussion at the earliest but having been through one bad experience he would probably like to first interact with the prospective brides? families and if they are comfortable they could then take the issue forward. His only condition is his insistence on an extremely simple marriage. Responses to this profile will be replied directly by him.
